Final Pipeline (8 files, 2,823 lines)                                                                          
                                                                                                               
  python run_pipeline.py          # runs everything in order                                                     
  python run_pipeline.py --step sanity   # just sanity check + overlap fix                                     
                                                                                                                 
  Execution Order                                                                                                
    Prostate_Cancer/2_Feature_Engineering/                                                                         
    config.py              ← cancer-specific settings (single source of truth)                                   
    0_run_pipeline.py      ← orchestrator (python 0_run_pipeline.py --step all)                                  
    1_sanity_check.py      ← overlap removal, dedup, sex/age filter                                              
    2_clean_data.py        ← lab range clamping, date parsing                                                    
    3_pipeline.py          ← generic FE functions (all cancers)                                                  
    4_cancer_features.py   ← prostate-specific features only                                                     
    5_cleanup.py           ← feature cleanup                                                                     
    6_text_features.py     ← NLP (keywords + TF-IDF + BERT)  

  The sanity check catches the issues that would silently corrupt the model if missed — especially the patient   
  overlap (same person in both cohorts = guaranteed leakage) and med-only patients (no clinical signal = noise in
   the training set).    